Author: jayclag0115
Title: ‚ö°Ô∏è[ANN]‚ö°Ô∏è REOS: Decentralized Ecosystem for User-Generated Content - Launched üì∏
Body: REOS is the world's first blockchain-based cryptographic exchange for digital content; a decentralized content platform that maximizes earning for content creators through tokenization of digital content  We help content creators and owners in three steps: o   Content Discovery & Exposure: Everyone interacts over a piece of content by commenting and reviewing with content promoter kicking off the content validation process. Everyone benefits by receiving tokens if acting responsibly. o   True Value Determination Combining Human & AI: Community-based content validation process + AI engine to determine value and projected sales o   Revenue Generation: Content is securely issued, distributed, and traded as tokens.  Revenue can be generated with license, pay-per-view, sponsorship and tipping. Majority of the revenue goes to the content creator. REOS charges a small transaction fee to support the platform and incentivize the content promoters.  let us know if you have more questions.

Author: REOSofficial
Title: ‚ö°Ô∏è[ANN]‚ö°Ô∏è REOS: Decentralized Ecosystem for User-Generated Content - Launched üì∏
Body: Hi, thank you for your question. We respect Steemit's success so far but we believe our platform is fundamentally different from Steemit in several aspects. First, Steemit is not truly decentralized. The problem lies with the distribution of Steem Power which, from the very start, was designed to concentrate among Steemit Inc. employees and developers. In 2017, it was estimated that the top 247 accounts on Steemit (most of which are probably owned by the developer and his ‚Äòfriends‚Äô through duplicate accounts) owned ~87.50% of total stake, without including the main Steemit account which is also controlled by the dev. (https://decentralize.today/the-ugly-truth-behind-steemit-1a525f5e156). In 2017, Oxfam calculated that just 8 people controlled the same wealth as 50% of the rest of the world. (https://steemit.com/steemit/@eroche/distribution-of-steem-and-steem-power). This means that a few people control the content on the Steemit platform. Imagine Warren Buffett's vote for a presidential nominee counts thousands more times than that of an average Joe. REOS, on the other hand, is truly democratic. Its unique "Voting with Stakes" mechanism ensures a democratic process of voting by community members. Each member puts in the same amount of REOS as stakes to vote for a piece of content, which means each vote counts the same.  The role of the Promoter is to initiate the voting (content validation) process and set the rules for the content validation (such as how long the voting process takes). We require that each Promoter has a minimum number of stakes (currently set at 100K REOS) because we want them to act responsibly. During the content validation period, the result is hidden from the community until the completion of the process. This ensures that we dig out the true worthiness of the content for the REOS community. On Steemit, users upvote or downvote for a piece of content and the voting power is based on the stakes a user owns. However, the users don't really lose stakes if they vote irresponsibly. On REOS, one can lose tokens if he or she votes irresponsibly. Our "Voting with Stakes" has some similarities to futures prediction markets, which have proven to be more accurate than polls.

Author: REOSofficial
Title: ‚ö°Ô∏è[ANN]‚ö°Ô∏è REOS: Decentralized Ecosystem for User-Generated Content - Launched üì∏
Body: Good question. REOSchain, the main blockchain for the REOS community, does ensure accurate attribution of ownership of digital assets. However, our platform goes way beyond that: we're building a decentralized user-generated content exchange with a content validation mechanism which not only allows for content creators to better monetize their content, but it also ensures the truthfulness of the content consumed by all members of the community. It's a platform for social UGC DApps where members of the community have complete control.  Our intro video explains what our strengths are quite well, feel free to check it out: https://youtu.be/xnHdIv_QHOo

Author: Sylon
Title: ‚ö°Ô∏è[ANN]‚ö°Ô∏è REOS: Decentralized Ecosystem for User-Generated Content - Launched üì∏
Body: Official website | Whitepaper   What is REOS? REOS is a blockchain-based ecosystem for user generated content (UGC) that empowers content creators and consumers. The platform enables content creators to monetize their UGC, such as short videos, in a variety of ways, without a middleman, while making sure that the content is validated by the REOS community. All digital content contributed by content creators are also registered on the REOSchain, the main blockchain for the REOS community, to ensure accurate attribution of ownership of the digital assets. Content creators can be securely paid by various stakeholders, bypassing any intermediaries, by using REOS, a utility crypto-token issued by REOS Foundation. The value of the content will be determined by the REOS community rather than by any central authority, thus honoring the belief that ‚ÄúTruth is Value.‚Äù   Our Mission Change the existing centralized, advertising-driven social media by leveraging blockchain technology to give power back to content creators and consumers while validating the truthfulness of the content.      Have any questions?   REOS Labs plans to issue a total of 10 billion pre-mined REOS tokens. Details of the token allocation will be published on https://reos.me/tokensale    REOS Token Uses ‚òÖContent Validation Process ‚òÖContent Licensing ‚òÖE-Commerce ‚òÖContent Creator Tipping/Sponsorship ‚òÖCrowd funding of Content Productions    FOLLOW US ON  Telegram | Twitter | LinkedIn | Medium   Note: I am making this original post for REOS. I am not the point of contact.
